"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is trying to plot date values on the x-axis, but matplotlib's plot function expects numerical values. To correctly plot dates, matplotlib's date2num function should be used to convert the dates to numerical values. Additionally, the plt.text function is being used with a datetime object which is not a valid x-coordinate.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n< ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n> import matplotlib.dates as mdates\\n> ax.plot(mdates.date2num(df['C']), df['E'])\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))\\n17c17\\n< plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\")), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"